review_blob: Hazy yellow pour from a bottle. Nice solid white head sticks around. Aroma is grassy with a perfect Belgian yeast. Palate of yeast, grassy hay. Brilliant ale is brilliant.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Wild Ale

review_blob: Nice amber appearance, little to no head retention, decent lacing. I get nearly nothing on the nose though, some caramel but thats about it. Taste is huge though, nice sweet malt up front, more caramel with a nice citrusy hop finish. Palate is heavy, thick a little creamy. Overall a good beer from Ninkasi.

Pours dark honey with a sturdy cream colored head. Aroma of malt, grassy, slight hops. Taste is huge caramel nice bitter finish in back of tongue warm alcohol remains. Mouthfeel is good and heavy. Overall this is quite a nice mistake if theyre to be believed. Is it a barleywine? Ipa? Strong ale?
Black pour with a mocha head. Aroma of coffee dark fruit.  Taste is huge chocolate with hints of coffee. Palate is nice and a bitterness lingers on the finish. Great imperial stout!

Poured from 750 into tulip. Very dark brown with creamy head. Aroma of dark fruits cherry plum. Oakiness and vanilla too. Taste is nice and mellow more of the oak vanilla and dark fruit really hides the 9% well. Mouthfeel is great drank it with some hearty irish beef stew and the beer cut through everything, really nice compliment. Quiet an amazing brew.

Hazy orange with a thin lacy head poured from 330mL can. Aroma is sweet maltiness. Taste is nice balance between malt and a great bitter finish. Mouthfeel is pillowy and perfect. Overall it really hides the 9.7% dangerously well and probably one of my favorite DIPAs.

Black pour with a red tinge nice off white head. Aroma of coffee chocolate. Taste is more chocolate and coffee but i also get a tobacco flavor on the end. Overall a great porter my go to for a drinkable affordable fantastic porter!
Pours nice orange with white head. Aroma of pears, apples, grass. Taste is sour first,  grassy and a nice clean mouth feel on the end. Overall its spectacular!

2008 750mL bottle from Portland Bottle Shop. Pours nice orange with floating yeast and/or spice. Aroma of pears, green apples, earthy. Head is HUGE and rocky, dissipates leaving nice lacing. Mouthfeel is great sweet then dry cut by hops. Overall an awesome beer and great overall.
Good hefe! Pours great cloudy golden w yeast suspended. Aroma of banana and cloves. Mouthfeel is nice could be a bit bigger but nice. Great hefeweizen freshing on a hot summer (or spring) afternoon.

Pours amber with a great big white head. Smell of wheat, yeast, bread, and hint of banana. Taste is in line with aroma. Great light mouth eel the wheat fights the sweetness. Great benchmark for the style.

750ml bottle best before: 15/11/12. Poured in a 12oz tulip. Great clear golden color. Aroma of hay, toffee, banana, orange peel. Taste is in line with aroma with a great dry finish. Just a touch of hop at the end. Overall one of the best tripels out there.

Poured from agood 750mL bottle into a tulip. A nice golden haze see the yeast floating! Nice soapy white head quickly dissipates leaving decent lacing. Aroma is malty and earthy with a little yeast. Taste is caramel malt with a nice dry bitter finish. Feels light on the palate with a nice carbonation. Great Belgian golden.

Poured into a tulip. Nice golden color with a good two finger head. From can (best art by any brewery imo). Decent lacing. Aroma of citrus and pine hops and toasted malt. Taste is citruses up front but a nice toasted honey cereal finish. Mouthfeel is medium and leaves a nice dry bitter finish.
beer_name: 21st Amendment Brew Free or Die IPA

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: 33 cl Bottle dated 18/3/11 poured into 12 oz tulip. Nice honey gold color. Two finger rocky white head. Taste is more grassy notes with a sweetness on the finish. A decent beer but not the best trappist blonde.

Very nice rye IPA. Poured into a standard 12oz. mug from 2012 bottle. appearance is a clear dark amber with a small white head that quickly dissipates leaving little to no lacing. Aroma is peppery, cereal rye (duh) and citrus hops, maybe a little caramel too. Taste goes with aroma, big peppery rye taste and a nice crisp citrus hop bitterness on the finish. Medium body with a average carbonation and a nice bitter finish. Overall a great rye IPA which will be perfect after work sitting outside on the first warm March afternoon of the spring. Extremely drinkable, will be enjoying this over and over, and will probably cut into my SN Torpedo consumption!
